{"data":{"post":{"id":"0ee46c0e-2d88-55bf-a7a3-e0b6efa61258","html":"<p>It’s not everyday that you see an artist like <strong><a href=\"http://www.suzannetreister.net/\">Suzanne Treister</a></strong> who delves into an exploration of human history woven into the paradigms of science, occult, technology and mass intelligence. Most contemporary artists nowadays have made artworks extracted from personal experience but <strong>Suzanne has definitely tackled on a mammoth undertaking to give us a view of our own distorted history.</strong></p>\n<p>I’ve been away because of my work at the <a href=\"http://www.london2012.com/festival\">Festival</a> but these are the type of exhibitions that I am excited to see. <strong>I am interested to see how Suzanne will tell our history through these tarot card illustrations</strong>. I’ve scheduled my visit at the <a href=\"http://www.sciencemuseum.org.uk/HEXEN2\">Science Museum</a> on 27 April – unfortunately the exhibition will end on 30 April so don’t miss this one. I just got the Suzanne Treister Hexen 2.0 book from Blackdog Publishing and it’s just one of those exhibitions were you want to see a preview of the book first. Because <strong>Suzanne Treister’s creative process is a combination of research</strong>, there are minutae details that you just want to take in first before seeing the actual work. I’m going to post the press release here so you can have a read but this will be updated as soon as I visit the exhibit. So watch this space.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/IMG_7554_ecmf0k-ba5a8ab1de27309f6bf48b2e9aba0b8f-33e24.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 480px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 114.16666666666666%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"IMG 7554 ecmf0k\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/IMG_7554_ecmf0k-ba5a8ab1de27309f6bf48b2e9aba0b8f-33e24.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/IMG_7554_ecmf0k-ba5a8ab1de27309f6bf48b2e9aba0b8f-7084e.jpg 200w,\n/static/IMG_7554_ecmf0k-ba5a8ab1de27309f6bf48b2e9aba0b8f-e263b.jpg 400w,\n/static/IMG_7554_ecmf0k-ba5a8ab1de27309f6bf48b2e9aba0b8f-33e24.jpg 480w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 480px) 100vw, 480px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>Here are some of the greatest illustrations I have ever seen in my life!</p>\n<p>\n  <figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n  \n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/http_momardi.com_wp-content_uploads_2012_04_TAROT_Hermit-TK_zu3x4q-b301283d28a34adc6f799a6a5d3f7c6e-d5a89.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; null; max-width: 485px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 164.94845360824743%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"http momardi com wp content uploads 2012 04 TAROT Hermit TK zu3x4q\"\n        title=\